NODE commands

npm init - inside the project folder to initialise the packages
npm install express  - to install express js for the current project

const express = require("express");
const app = express();

to include express in the web app


app.listen(3800, function(){
	console.log("server started on 3800");
});


this will set up the server on which port you want to run

to run the server

node  filename.js ----everytime you make change in the webapp you need to manually restart the server

nodemon filename.js ---automatically restarts the server